	<Title>
		Recipe: Orange roughy with lemon and thyme
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Orange roughy with lemon and thyme &amp;mdash; one of many healthy recipes from Mayo Clinic.
	</Abstract>
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		2
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; One serving of this broiled orange roughy has about 100 calories and 1 gram of fat. To make it a meal, add steamed fresh green beans, roasted red potatoes, whole-wheat rolls and lime sherbet. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
Preheat the broiler (grill). Position the rack 4 inches from the heat source. Lightly coat a baking sheet with cooking spray. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Place the fish on the prepared baking sheet. Squeeze the juice from 2 lemon wedges over the fillets. Sprinkle with thyme. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Broil (grill) until the fish is opaque throughout when tested with a tip of a knife, about 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from the oven. Garnish with the two remaining lemon wedges and serve immediately. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2 orange roughy fillets, each 4 ounces&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 lemon, cut into 4 wedges&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 teaspoon fresh thyme, chopped&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
